label: Erastus Everson Diary 1861-1893, page 211
description: A color scan of a scrapbook page with a letter from Major William Stone and an annotation by Everson.  The letter from Stone requests Everson and Governor Robert K. Scott's endorsement of a Mr. Edmondston--who has been disenfranchised--for office as they both have influence within Congress.  Both Stone and Everson write of the wrongly placed lack of support for politicians from the south.
